Patrick Winston’s How to Speak talk has been an MIT tradition for over 40 years. Offered every January, 
the talk is intended to improve your speaking ability in critical situations by teaching you a few heuristic rules.


- 00:16 – Introduction
- 03:11 – Rules of Engagement
- 04:15 – How to Start
- 05:38 – Four Sample Heuristics
- 10:17 – The Tools: Time and Place
